Package: LSFoFQR
Type: Package
Title: Locally Sparse Function-on-Function Quantile Regression
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: c(
    person("Ufuk", "Beyaztas",
      email = "ufuk.beyaztas@marmara.edu.tr",
      role = c("aut", "cre", "cph"),
      comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0002-5208-4950"))
  )
Description: Functions for fitting locally sparse simultaneous
    function-on-function quantile regression models. The package implements a
    three-stage estimation framework for functional responses and functional
    predictors, where the quantile-varying regression kernel is represented by
    tensor-product B-spline bases over the predictor, response, and quantile
    domains. Smoothness is controlled through directional P-spline penalties,
    while local sparsity is induced by an adaptive multiplicity-balanced
    overlapping group-Lasso penalty acting on cuboidal blocks of spline
    coefficients. Estimation proceeds through a smooth pilot fit, an adaptive
    locally sparse fit, and a constrained refit on the selected active
    coefficient set. The package provides functions for constructing the
    required B-spline bases, fitting the proposed model, selecting tuning
    parameters by a QBIC-type criterion, extracting estimated coefficient
    surfaces, predicting conditional quantile response curves for new
    functional predictors, and generating simulated data from a functional
    location-scale model with known quantile-varying coefficient surfaces.
Depends: R (>= 3.5.0)
Imports:
    Matrix,
    MASS,
    splines,
    stats
